          My two cents .. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uh0110w.showPublicProfile?language=EN>h0110w</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/h0110w_3q/Watching.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/19/02 11:41:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/h0110w_3q/Phirean.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot rules, to be or not to be?</span><hr size=1> I don't want to kick a dead horse, nor start and argument, but I'm constantly amazed that people don't like doing raids just for the hell of it. Not that I'm trying to change anybody's opinion, I see a lot of posts that both agree or disagree, and that's fine. Warpath: you don't really need to worry about changing your rules to get more people to come. Provided you post on the registry that you're doing a dragon, well enough in advance, you'll get enough people to come who won't need to roll for a different character, if that's the issue. No, I'm not saying that rolling for an alt is wrong, but if your intent is to get some lower level characters some higher level gear, then by all means do so. I'll be there either way, provided I still have characters in the necessary range, and have the time. Killing a dragon is fun. Meeting new people is fun. Doing both at the same time is, you guessed it, fun. I'm here to play a game, and enjoy my time doing so, and I know quite a few people that are of the same mind.<br>
